it plays like a tony hawk game; perform a grab or flip trick while spinning in midair. each stunt is worth a certain amount of points, with each 180 degree spin adding 180 points to its baseline. performing a combo of stunts will multiply your points by the number of them performed. you receive those points on a successful landing. grab tricks will accumulate points the longer you hold and/or spin with them, while flips only add points per spin. your arrow keys are mapped exactly how the right half of a controller is laid out. ive been meaning to make a tutorial level but i think i'll program it for v005 as i'm currently crunched for v0041. in the meantime, there's a "How to Play" button on the menu that shows you the controls. Anybody with a high air and speed stat will help you with ramps. i like playtesting with Gwen as she's well rounded, but if you don't have her unlocked, Emma works too. Lauren and Morgan are fantastic for vert thanks to their large airtime. either way, experiment with each skater and see how they play!
